Prompt # I didn&rsquo;t know that strings was a command until way later LMAO. ¯\_(ツ)_/¯
Solution #As the name suggests, this challenge&rsquo;s purpose is to jump-start the reversing category. I decided to start the challenge by following the prompt and printing the ASCII strings the binary contains, and filter for the flag format.
$ strings sanity-check | grep &#34;UACTF&#34; UACTF{N3V3R_G0NN4_L37_Y0U_D0WN}
